task.summary:
BIG COMMIT
Added Command/SubCommand System: - All "/guilds" subcommands have their own class and must follow the system. Created GeneralMethods class. Updated Guilds.java for new command system.

Updated the database table layout Added language and config options Created the create command Added the getCurrentDate() method Added the CommandExecutor to Commands.java
NEED TO FIX COMMANDS NOT REGISTERING (Nothing happens when a command is done, literally nothing...)

Command System Update - Fixed the commands not registering by registering them after the database and config were set up & connected and by changing "new Commands(this);" to "new Commands(plugin);" - All SubCommands must have their base subcommand in their aliases. - Allowed the "sendingArgs" subList to contain 0 args -> args.length instead of 1 so command wouldn't error when doing the base command only.*** - Added enabled message to end of Commands(plugin).
***THIS WILL CHANGE WHEN WE ADD COMMAND BASE FUNCTION/METHOD!!!!
Almost fully finished CreateCommand.java, then I will be onto RemoveCommand.java. Removed the time from getCurrentDate(). Added base command help. Fixed SQL errors

General Fixes: CreateCommand: - Added inAGuild() check - Added guildExists() check - Added guild to the guilds HashSet that will be loaded when the server loads the plugin. GuildsCommand: - Added isGuildLeader() - Added inAGuild() (COMING SOON, NOT STARTED) - Added loadLeaders() (EXECUTES ON PLUGIN LOAD) - Added guildExists() - Added getGuilds() (GETS THE GUILDS DATABASE) - Added loadGuilds() (EXECUTES ON PLUGIN LOAD) Guilds: - Added GuildsCommand.loadGuilds(); to the enable sequence. - Added GuildsCommand.loadLeaders(); to the enable sequence.

General Fixes: - Added GuildsCommand.guilds.add(guildName) and GuildsCommand.leaders.add(leader) to CreateCommand.java - Made the HelpCommand java executor. - Removed the not needed balance in SQL Table creation.
DBConnection Fix: - Fixed the extra '`' in the code of guilds_players and updated the MySQL version to the same thing.
Remove not needed portion in create command.

General Changes: - Combined lines in CreateCommand.java so it was easier to read. - Removed some things in Language Config that are not needed yet (I thought we could just add them as we actually implement the feature) - Changed names around in Language Config to more organized. - Fixed Typo: changing "prfixError" to "prefixError".

General Changes pt2: - Fixed CreateCommand Errors and also switched to the GuildUtils.sendMessage() instead of sender.sendMessage(). - Deleted unfinished commands, made it so the description is configurable. - Getting Ready to start the InfoCommand.java file. - Simplified the GuildsCommand.java and also used GuildUtils.sendMessage() instead of sender.sendMessage(). - Errors must be in &C (Red (not dark)). - Normal command descriptions must be in &e (Yellow). - Successes must be in &a (Green (not dark)). - Made enum Prefix easier to read.
General Changes pt3: - Forgot to add GuildUtils.color() to HelpCommand descriptions.

Added aliases to all current commands: - Admin Command Aliases: - "a", "staff", "mod". - Create Command Aliases: - "new", "n", "start". - Help Command Aliases: - "?", "h". - Info Command Aliases: - "about", "i".

Started on the Info Command... The main thing we need to do is create all of the methods so that we can check for the information. TODO METHODS: - boolean isGuild Method. - boolean isPlayer Method. - void getPlayerBalance Method. - void getGuildBalance Method. - void getUserGuild Method. - void getPreviousGuild Method. - void getGuildLeader Method. - void getGuildApprentices Method. - void getGuildClaimedChunks Method. - void getGuildMembers Method.
PICTURES FOR WHAT THE INFO COMMAND WILL LOOK LIKE: - https://gyazo.com/b6e6daabfef8578c38266b4962e57c07 (guild) - https://gyazo.com/b93b03b164793980309e6d4f76ae022e (player)

Did List Command: - The list command executes and starts off with getting a list of all of the guilds provided by the new getGuilds() method, then it sends a list of all of the guilds. *** Works on my test server. - Added List Command to GuildsCommand.java - Added Lang Config Option for the List Description. - Added the GET_GUILDS SqlQuery.
